You're missing the `BindingContext`. Your page doesn't know which ViewModel to bind against.

**Fix:** Set the `BindingContext` in your code-behind:

```csharp
public partial class MyPage : ContentPage
{
    public MyPage(MyViewModel vm)
    {
        InitializeComponent();
        BindingContext = vm;
    }
}
```

**Also ensure** your ViewModel implements `INotifyPropertyChanged` (or uses `[ObservableProperty]` from the MVVM Community Toolkit) so the UI updates when properties change.
